title: Comparing Boxplots: Words Typed Per Minute Between Boys and Girls
question_text:
Jessica collected data on the number of words typed per minute with zero mistakes in her typing class. Using the data, Jessica generated the boxplots below.
Which of the following statements must be TRUE?

choices.text:
The mean number of words typed per minute with zero mistakes for the females in Jessica's typing class is
53
.

The IQR of the number of words typed per minute with zero mistakes for the females in Jessica's typing class is
34
.

There is a higher percentage of males students in Jessica's typing class that type less than
45
words per minute without making a mistake than females do.

There are a lower percentage of females in Jessica's typing class that type at least
64
words per minute without making a mistake than males do.

The range for the males in this data is
15
.
